               <history>
                 <origin><origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1674">1085 AH (1674 CE)</origDate></origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>While the circumstances under which this volume arrived in Britain remain unclear, <orgName>King's College</orgName> Professor of Oriental Languages <persName type="standard"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/66617580/" key="person_66617580" role="fmo"
                        change="#role-assignment">Duncan Forbes (1798–1868)</persName>, who
                        describes the volume in his published catalogue (p. 36, no. 109), before
                        he sold his manuscript collection to his publisher <orgName role="bsl"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/152259747" key="person_152259747"><persName
                              key="person_45159035185601380002" role="bsl" change="#prov-markup">W.
                              H. Allen </persName>&amp; Co.</orgName> in exchange for an annuity.
                        Subsequently sold by that firm to <persName type="standard"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/" key="person_97751058" role="fmo"
                           change="#role-assignment">Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford
                           (1812–1880)</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1866"
                              >1866</date>
                     </p>
                  </provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Purchased by <persName role="dnr" key="person_f6379" change="#prov-markup"
                     >Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian"
                        when="1901">1901</date> from <persName role="fmo"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/" key="person_9985420">James Ludovic
                           Lindsay, 26th Earl of Crawford (1847–1913)</persName>.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Bequeathed by <persName key="person_f6379" change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta Rylands
                        (1843–1908)</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1908"
